'''Alternative for Change''' ({{lang-es|Alternativa por el Cambio}} - AC), formerly known as "Christian Alternative," is a [[Nicaragua]]n [[political party]].<ref name=siegel>{{Cite web|url=http://digitalcollections.sit.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1310&context=isp_collection|title=Searching for a Path: Evangelicals in Nicaraguan Politics|author=Jacob Siegel|date=2006-10-01|accessdate=2011-08-25}}</ref>

It was founded by dissidents from the [[Nicaraguan Party of the Christian Path]] (CCN), most notably [[Orlando Tardencilla]].<ref name=siegel/> In the [[Nicaraguan general election, 2006|2006 presidential elections]], the party fielded [[Edén Pastora]] as its presidential candidate, <ref>{{cite book|last=Hendrix|first=Steven E.|title=The new Nicaragua: lessons in development, democracy, and nation-building for the United States|year=2009|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-37958-1|pages=75|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pZ0lybB9UGkC&pg=PA75&dq=%22Alternativa+por+el+Cambio%22&hl=en&ei=RJJVTqekJNG4hAfusMWUBg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&sqi=2&ved=0CC4Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Alternativa%20por%20el%20Cambio%22&f=false}}</ref> but Pastora only managed to obtain 0.27% of the vote.<ref name=siegel/><ref>{{cite book|last=Seligson|first=Mitchell A.|first2=Orlando J.|last2=Pérez|title=Cultura política de la democracia en Nicaragua 2008: El impacto de la Gobernabilidad|year=2008|publisher=LAPOP|isbn=0-9817299-3-2|pages=185|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=88gYo2VN6pIC&pg=PA185&dq=%22Alternativa+por+el+Cambio%22&hl=en&ei=RJJVTqekJNG4hAfusMWUBg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&sqi=2&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=%22Alternativa%20por%20el%20Cambio%22&f=false}}</ref>

