The '''Avadānaśataka''' or "Century of Noble Deeds ([[Avadana|Avadāna]])" is an anthology in Sanskrit of one hundred [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] legends, approximately dating to the same time as the [[Ashokavadana]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Strong|first=John S. |authorlink=John S. Strong|title=The Legend of King Asoka|publisher=[[Princeton University Press]]|year=1983|page=31|ISBN=9780691605074}}</ref> The work may be from the [[Mulasarvastivada]] school.<ref>{{cite book|last=Schopen|first=Gregory|title=Buddhist Monks and Business Matters: Still More Papers on Monastic Buddhism in India|publisher=[[University of Hawaii Press]]|page=125|year=2004|ISBN=9780824825478}}</ref>

